Note: AWS CloudFront is great for serving http servers to secure websites over https

We are putting CloudFront in front of our EC2 endpoint (think of it like an adapter) in order to serve that endpoint via the HTTPS protocol
Amplify is by default using the HTTPS protocol and browsers (like Chrome) don't allow for HTTPS to HTTP (or vice versa) communication.
This is referred to as "Mixed Content" - https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Security/Mixed_content
How to fix this situation according to MDN - https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Security/Mixed_content/How_to_fix_website_with_mixed_content

CLOUDFRONT
Create Distribution -> get started 
In the Origin Domain Name section, add your EC2 url endpoint (if you go to your EC2 service console this is under Public IPv4 DNS / address)
